title: Census Bureau: School Enrollment in the United States: 2014
text:
U.S. Census Bureau
WASHINGTON , Oct. 15, 2015 /PRNewswire-USNewswire/ -- The following tip sheet was released today by the U.S. Census Bureau:
These tables provide information by age, sex, race, Hispanic origin, family income, type of college, employment status, nativity, foreign-born parentage, attendance status (full or part time), type of school (public or private), and vocational course enrollment. They also delve into topics such as nursery school and kindergarten enrollment, the likelihood of being enrolled in a grade appropriate for their age and the percentage of young adults enrolled in college. Historical tables are also provided. Internet address: http://www.census.gov/hhes/school/index.html .
No news release associated with this product. Tip Sheet only.
